Package: arframe
Title: A Regulatory Frame for TFLs
Version: 0.1.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Vignesh", "Thanikachalam", email = "about.vignesh@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Produces regulatory-grade clinical trial tables, listings, and
    figures (TLFs) in RTF and PDF from a single specification. Designed for
    pharmaceutical industry workflows with support for paginated output,
    spanning headers, decimal alignment, programmatic page headers/footers,
    and company-specific rule presets. PDF rendering uses XeLaTeX with
    automatic Adobe open-source font fallback; set the 'ARFRAME_FONT_DIR'
    environment variable to use project-local fonts without system-wide
    installation. Built on disciplined S3 classes with a clean, composable
    pipeline API. No 'dplyr', 'tidyr', or 'purrr' dependency — only
    lightweight infrastructure packages ('rlang', 'cli', 'vctrs').
SystemRequirements: XeLaTeX (optional, for PDF output only; tinytex
    recommended)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
